<br>
The next morning we woke up to snow and sleet which didn't last long.  got another fire going and ate breakfast waiting for the water to drop and getting warm.  We hit the laundry mat that morning to dry out our waders and clothes and then fished by the dam.  Caught the krap out of bows.  We then headed to cow shoals again and found a couple of holes above the acccess on the right side of the river and procedded to catch more browns.  Some good ones in the 15 to 22 inch range.  We were getting strikes about every other cast.  <br>
<br>
Our best fish 22' brown that troutstalker caught.  fished by the dam on thursday morn for a couple of hours and headed home.  We took a boat and never put it in the water.  Our tarp was tied to it.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
All in all a heck of a fun trip on some different water.  Thanks to John W. for showing us the good spots.<br>
